{title: Christ the Lord Is Risen Today}
{subtitle: Charles Wesley, 1739 — Easter Hymn from Lyra Davidica (1708)}
{key: C}
{time: 4/4}
{tempo: 96}
{comment: Each line is answered with a melismatic "Alleluia." Easter Day hymn.}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[C]Christ the [F]Lord is [C]risen to[G]day, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Sons of [F]men and [C]angels [G]say, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Raise your [F]joys and [C]triumphs [G]high, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Sing, ye [F]heavens, and [C]earth, re[G]ply, Alle[C]lu[G]ia![C]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
[C]Love's re[F]deeming [C]work is [G]done, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Fought the [F]fight, the [C]battle [G]won, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Death in [F]vain for[C]bids Him [G]rise, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Christ has [F]opened [C]para[G]dise, Alle[C]lu[G]ia![C]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
[C]Lives a[F]gain our [C]glorious [G]King, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Where, O [F]death, is [C]now thy [G]sting? Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Once He [F]died our [C]souls to [G]save, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Where thy [F]victo[C]ry, O [G]grave? Alle[C]lu[G]ia![C]
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
[C]Soar we [F]now where [C]Christ has [G]led, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Following [F]our ex[C]alted [G]Head, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Made like [F]Him, like [C]Him we [G]rise, Alle[C]lu[G]ia!
[C]Ours the [F]cross, the [C]grave, the [G]skies, Alle[C]lu[G]ia![C]
{end_of_verse}
